          "author_association": "OWNER",
          "body": "Filed from the pd-book-tools deep code/security review.\n\n    Report: `pd-book-tools/docs/research/2026-05-22-deep-code-security-review.md`\n    Finding: #7\n\n    ## Summary\n\n    The GPU job does not install the gpu extra, then imports cupy, and tests skip CUDA when CI is detected.\n\n    ## Impact\n\n    GPU CI either fails before tests or gives false confidence; CUDA regressions can land untested.\n\n    ## Evidence\n\n    - `.gitlab-ci.yml:46`\n- `.gitlab-ci.yml:49`\n- `pyproject.toml:56`\n- `tests/conftest.py:140`\n- `tests/conftest.py:153`\n\n    ## Acceptance\n\n    - [ ] Use uv sync --group dev --extra gpu in the GPU job.\n- [ ] Replace blanket CI skips with CUDA availability checks or GPU_CI=1.\n- [ ] Revisit allow_failure for GPU regressions.\n\n    ## Notes\n\n    This issue was filed from a read-only review. Confirm behavior with a focused failing test before implementation where practical.",
          "closed_at": "2026-05-22T16:03:51Z",
